DEFINITIONS

"The Game" refers to Cubon, developed by Cotordo Games, including all official
releases, updates, and associated content.

"The Codebase" refers to the source code, scripts, and engine logic contained
within this repository.

"Non-Code Assets" refers to all assets that are not source code, including but
not limited to: artwork, sprites, tilesets, music, sound effects, voice acting,
story content, character designs, and world/level data belonging to The Game.

"Derivative Work" refers to any project, tool, game, or software that is based
on, incorporates, or is derived from The Codebase.

"You" refers to any individual or entity accessing, using, or modifying The
Codebase.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

PERMISSIONS

You ARE permitted to:

1. STUDY — Read, analyze, and learn from The Codebase for any purpose,
   including personal and educational use.

2. MODIFY — Fork and modify The Codebase for personal use or to create
   Derivative Works, provided all other terms of this license are followed.

3. RELEASE DERIVATIVE WORKS — Publish games or tools built using The Codebase,
   provided they do not incorporate Non-Code Assets from The Game and are not
   monetized in any form.

4. MOD AND PATCH — Create and distribute mods, patches, bugfixes, or
   extensions that are designed to be applied to an existing licensed copy of
   The Game, provided such mods do not reproduce or repackage The Game itself.

5. PORT THE CODEBASE — Translate or port The Codebase to other programming
   languages or platforms for study or non-commercial use, provided the full
   game experience is not reproduced or redistributed as a result.

6. CREDIT AND SHARE — Share, link to, or discuss The Codebase publicly,
   provided proper credit is given.

